refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
callablemeth_caller stringclass_name stringmethod_name
meth_caller takes a class name and a method name, and returns a callable which will invoke that method on any object of that class passed to the callable. (This is hard to explain, see examples below.) Like fun, this is in order to aide the typechecker in statically analyzing callbacks passed into and out of functions.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Simple meth_caller usage:


<?hh

class C {
  function f(): string {
    return 'hi test';
  }
}

function test(): void {
  $c = new C();

  // meth_caller will invoke method 'f' on objects of type 'C'.
  $f = meth_caller('C', 'f');
  echo $f($c); // Prints "hi test"
}







    More realistic callback usage:


<?hh

function run_callback((function (C): string) $f, C $c) {
  return $f($c);
}

function test2(): void {
  $c = new C();

  // A more realistic example, where meth_caller can be used to generate a
  // callback that can be passed around with full type information.
  $f = meth_caller('C', 'f');
  echo run_callback($f, $c); // Prints "hi test"
}







    meth_caller used as callback for a map:


<?hh

$v = Vector {
  Vector {42, 42, 42},
  Vector {42}
};

$v->map(meth_caller('Vector', 'count')); // returns Vector {3, 1}
